    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Designation used for painters in 14th- through 18th-century northern and southern Europe who painted the main subjects of art works, distinguished from "coarse painters," who specialized in decorative work. The categories were defined within the painters' guild of St. Luke.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
